    "client_msg_id": "63E2E536-4962-4849-884C-59B83F455347",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I think there's plenty of good critiques here, but I do want to point out that ‘Web3’ is a very broad umbrella term that's often used for disingenuous marketing hype.\n\nThere's just such a big chasm between the voices in the space that get millions-billions in VC funding vs the really interesting work going on a bit under the surface.\n\nE.g. Ceptr, Holochain, Protocol Labs/IPFS/IPLD, Commons Stack (as one of many groups oriented around commons and public goods), etc.\n\nSo many really great researchers and research communities that have a lot to offer our community here. And vice versa.\n\nIt's about a lot more than decentralisation or currency and `Web3 != crypto`. it's sad to see so much public attention around the _least_ interesting parts of the space like bitcoin or etherium or the many predatory businesses that have emerged.",
    "user": "U014WA16VNJ",
    "ts": "1641693741.013200",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
