  {
    "client_msg_id": "4ac18241-688c-4b0d-b3fc-d4757060d896",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "It would be great if the people doing interesting research in this space could come up with a label different from \"web3\". But some of them seem to be clearly riding on the \"web3\" wave, perhaps because of the visibility this gives. IPFS, for example, is a project I have been following for years with much interest (and I am even using it a bit), but I am not so happy about their communication which is very much \"IPFS is a complement to blockchains\".",
    "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
    "ts": "1641724345.023200",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_profile": {
